    {
      "id": "PopularPost248138",
      "post_content": "@reapersaurus: No. Just... No. Thing is, combining [Giant Growth](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Giant Growth) and [Assault Strobe](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Assault Strobe) would cost you **two** separate cards. Two cards which you may not have in your hand at the same time. Combining them in one card effectively gives you +1 card advantage and may open up four additional card slots in your deck to use for other cards, not to mention that this combination of effects is actually quite powerful. These advantages are worth an increased mana cost. But to print this card at your price would simply **obsolete** both Giant Growth and Assault Strobe in a ![Red or Green](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=RG&type=symbol) deck, and possibly a ![Green](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=G&type=symbol) deck that splashes ![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol) or vice versa. It would be, quite simply, what we call **borderline broken**.  \n  \nThough I agree with what other commenters have said. This could at least have been an instant.",
      "posted_by": "Tiggurix",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost248138\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_post\">@reapersaurus: No. Just... No. Thing is, combining <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Giant Growth\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Giant Growth\">Giant Growth</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Assault Strobe\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Assault Strobe\">Assault Strobe</a> would cost you <b>two</b> separate cards. Two cards which you may not have in your hand at the same time. Combining them in one card effectively gives you +1 card advantage and may open up four additional card slots in your deck to use for other cards, not to mention that this combination of effects is actually quite powerful. These advantages are worth an increased mana cost. But to print this card at your price would simply <b>obsolete</b> both Giant Growth and Assault Strobe in a <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red or Green\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=RG&amp;type=symbol\"/> deck, and possibly a <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Green\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=G&amp;type=symbol\"/> deck that splashes <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=R&amp;type=symbol\"/> or vice versa. It would be, quite simply, what we call <b>borderline broken</b>.<br/><br/>Though I agree with what other commenters have said. This could at least have been an instant.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '248138'); return false;\">\